tldr: The agent successfully implemented several new features for the
  SomnaHealth sleep questionnaire, including a tiredness severity scale, COMISA
  detection, insufficient sleep syndrome detection, weighted EDS scoring,
  expanded CSV export, pain/chronic fatigue screening, and medical/mental health
  history sections. The implementation addressed all identified gaps from the
  initial review.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and an existing Statement of
  Work. The agent identified several critical missing features and gaps in the
  current implementation. Subsequently, the agent proceeded to implement these
  features, including a granular tiredness severity scale with safety warnings,
  advanced detection logic for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and a
  weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness. The data export
  functionality was significantly enhanced to include all questionnaire
  responses, and new sections were added to capture pain, chronic fatigue
  symptoms, and comprehensive medical/mental health history. Each implementation
  step involved updating data types, validation schemas, user interface
  components, and report generation logic (both on-screen and PDF), ensuring the
  application now fully meets the specified acceptance criteria.
